                <mxCell id="102" value="&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;This UML diagram demonstrates the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;critical path&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;of a request in a multi-threaded web server, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;as every request passes through&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;bounded buffer&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;, interacting with listener and worker threads. This critical path is often a bottleneck&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;that determines server &lt;br&gt;performance and efficiency, and is significantly affected by the scheduling policies that our research extension into&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;First-Come-First-Serve and Shortest-File-First explores.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;resizable=0;points=[];autosize=1;strokeColor=#666666;fillColor=#f5f5f5;fontFamily=Verdana;fontSize=13;glass=0;fontColor=#333333;shadow=1;rounded=1;arcSize=25;horizontal=1;spacing=2.0000000000000004;spacingTop=10;spacingBottom=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="33" y="95" width="866" height="90" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
